de.tuberlin.onedrivesdk.folder

Class ConcreteOneFolder

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.tuberlin.onedrivesdk.common.OneItem
      • de.tuberlin.onedrivesdk.folder.ConcreteOneFolder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OneFolder

    public class ConcreteOneFolder
extends OneItem
implements OneFolder
    Here goes everything that is needed for every resource Like all the communication with the server and handling the requests and parsing them to simple JSONObjects The childClasses then will form themselves according to the JSONObject by picking what they need and ignoring what isn't relevant for them Like If this item represents a folder, a folder child will use the JSONObject with all the folder data to fill it's own fields
